The paper deals with the problem of index coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also involves the study of graphs and graph parameters, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper introduces and studies two restricted models of index coding, which can be considered as topics in systems and control (cs.SI) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
